      <akn:section eId="sec_28:2A_219">
        <akn:num>28:2A-219</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Risk of loss.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_28:2A-219_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Except in the case of a finance lease, risk of loss is retained by the lessor and does not pass to the lessee. In the case of a finance lease, risk of loss passes to the lessee.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_28:2A-219_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Subject to the provisions of this article on the effect of default on risk of loss (§ 28:2A-220), if risk of loss is to pass to the lessee and the time of passage is not stated, the following rules apply:</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
